glazes, and a pharmaceutic alkalizer

A white porous form of limestone made of calcite
and the skeletons of billions of plankton that
settled to the sea floor. Can be used in pottery
glazing, decomposed into slaked lime, in agriculture to raise pH,
and to confuse college students on a blackboard

extracted and used in the creation of
particularly strong or conductive alloys
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_phosphorite.des:
Also known as phosphate rock,
it is a crucial resource in the
production of industrial fertilizer
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_fluorspar.desc:
Used to produce hydrogen fluoride,
an important chemical in many
industrial processes
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_zirconia.desc:
It is mostly made of zirconium dioxide
and is among the most well known materials for
electroceramics and certain thermal barrier coatings
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_germanite.desc:
Named for its germanium content. Not the main
source, but still has a good amount
of the element for superconductor creation
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_spodumene.desc:
It is one of the most common sources of lithium.
It looks ash-gray which earned its name
from the greek 'spodumenos', or 'burnt to ashes'
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_petalite.desc:
Somewhat similar to spodumene, it's a great source of
lithium and is used in ceramic glazes
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_lepidolite.desc:
The most common mineral containing lithium.
It is also the primary source of rubidium.
(The element, not the minecraft mod)
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_amblygonite.des:
A fluorophosphate mineral, it's sometimes used as a
source of lithium. Often confused with feldspar
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_oil_sands.desc:
A lump of loose sand and clay mostly held
together by bitumen, very dense petroleum that
has been used since the Paleolithic as an
adhesive and waterproofing material
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_kerogen.desc:
Highly compacted organic matter, it is an essential
part of the carbon cycle and on a geological time scale,
it eventually breaks down into many compounds,
including most fossil fuels
item.nyagibits_bytes.ancient_fossil.desc:
The mineralized imprint of a long gone life form.
Although it is not quite clear what it used to
be, more careful processing is required
item.nyagibits_bytes.end_organic_mush.de:
An assortment of decomposed matter from the
End, mostly chorus. Mycelial cords from various End
fungal species are dispersed within, perhaps
they could be isolated...
item.nyagibits_bytes.ender_pumice.desc:
A very porous volcanic rock formed
by rapidly cooling lava trapping gas bubbles
within. This particular sample seems to be made of
End stone...are there volcanoes in the End?
A lot of data about the history of the
world can be gained by studying samples like
this one, like a geological time capsule. This should
prove very useful in your research...
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_monazite.desc:
A collection of phosphates containing rare earths,
most prominently cerium. Other common mozanites bear
lanthanum, neodynium, samarium and praseodymium
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_cerite.desc:
A complex silicate mineral containing cerium,
although varieties rich in lanthanum exist as well
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_allanite.desc:
A sorosilicate group of minerals known for their
high concentration of rare earths, up to 20%
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_bastnasite.desc:
One of the more common rare earth carbonates,
named after the Bastnäs mine, responsible for the
discovery of many minerals
item.nyagibits_bytes.raw_xenotime.desc:
Host to a myriad of rare earths, any resemblance
to a certain light absorbing fictional creature
made of black crystals is purely coincidental

instructions to channel specific
types of energy

This rune has optically relevant
artificial crystals within able
to down-convert mana to specific
wavelength photons
item.nyagibits_bytes.rune_velocity.desc:
This rune is able to modify its
own velocity through mana conversion
item.nyagibits_bytes.rune_inertia.desc:
Much like a gyroscope this rune
is able to maintain a moment of
inertia in one axis
Using mana this rune basically
functions like a heat exchanger
you would see in a refrigerator
item.nyagibits_bytes.rune_magnetic.desc:
The electromagnetic coils in
this rune seem to function much
more efficiently when manasteel
is within the structure
item.nyagibits_bytes.rune_catalytic.desc:
Similar to 'on-carbon' catalysts
this rune is able to use mana to
swap which materials are expressed
on the surface for any given reaction
